context_C:
Formally, we define a state machine as (S,X,Y,_0,,) where

- S is a finite or infinite set of possible states;
- X is a finite or infinite set of possible inputs;
- Y is a finite or infinite set of possible outputs;
- s_0 S is the initial state of the machine;
- f: S x X S is a transition function, which takes an input and a previous state and produces a next state;
